  "text": "Nasopharyngeal carcinoma (NPC) is one of the most common malignant tumors, with its incidence rate ranking first among head and neck cancers. In China, more than 90% of NPC cases are pathological type III according to the World Health Organisation (WHO) criteria, and are sensitive to radiation. Therefore, for patients who are newly diagnosed and without metastasis, radiotherapy is the preferred treatment [CITATION_1] . In the last decade, the effect of NPC radiotherapy has been significantly improved. The local control rate of early NPC is 70-90%, while that of T3-4 NPC is 50% [CITATION_2] .",
